main event: A sighting of an unidentified aerial phenomenon occurred over Mount Vernon, New York on June 25, 1963.
interesting points: The object was observed for about 5 minutes,They believed the object could have been a balloon, satellite, or aircraft overshoot,The object moved too rapidly for any conventional spacecraft,The object was described as 'white, circular' and positioned in front of the moon during a later sighting,The sighting report acknowledges it was not an aircraft.
witness description: A civilian who reported seeing a rapidly moving star-like object.
